<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">binding and finishing</a>, the process of assembling printed <a title="Signature" href="Signature">signature</a>s and placing them in the correct sequence for binding. Gathering is often performed by automated gathering machines which operate much like collating machines: each signature placed in a different pocket, and after all the pockets have been filled, the machine assembles them in the desired sequence. A type of gathering in which signatures are wrapped around other signatures (such as the prelude to <a title="Saddle-Stitching" href="Saddle-Stitching">saddle-stitching</a>) is called <a title="Inserting" href="Inserting">inserting</a>, while the gathering of individual sheets (rather than of signatures) is called <a title="Collating" href="Collating">collating</a>. See <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">Binding and Finishing</a>. 
</p>
